1) INTRODUCTION\
\
The goal of the game is to put as many words on the board as possible. \
Playing is easy, if you know how to play Bananagrams and/or Scrabble, \
than you should have no problems playing this game. However, to win you \
will need to think outside the box (or /inside/ the box in this case). \
The goal of the game is to place as many words as possible in the \
smallest area possible, using letters as efficiently as possible. \
\
\
2) GAME PLAY\
\
Every turn you will be given letters up the up to the size of your \
board. From these you must pick those you wish to place on the board. On \
the first turn, your word must intersect the starting character '@'. On \
every subsequent turn your word must intersect some portion of the what \
is already on the board. Words may overlap, be lengthened and can even \
be overwritten. Be careful though, you the total number of letters you \
get is equal to the number of spots on your board.\
\
When playing words, you must specify:\
- The WORD with quotes (" or ')\
- The COLUMN (A,B,C,D,..etc.)\
- The ROW number\
- What AXIS you want your letters placed on (X or Y)\
\
If you are stuck you also have the option to #TRASH letters that you \
can't use. \
