\cf0 3) WINNING\
\
At the end of play the number of correctly spelled words on the board \
will be tallied and scored according to the per letter point-values of \
Scrabble. Incorrectly spelled words will be subtracted from this score. \
You word-score will then by your by the area of the board (hence the \
name "Lexical-Density").\
\
When calculating the Lexical-Density of the board, any adjacent sequence \
of letters will be counted as a word. All 'words' will be checked \
against the SOWPODS dictionary, so regular Scrabble rules apply in terms \
of word choice.\
\
4) SAVING\
\
You may #SAVE your game at anytime. Players using a specified 'tag' are \
able to save multiple completed games, and will be able to see pertinent \
statistics across them.\
